obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (27008)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27008&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Union territories`
  line `(Separation of Judicial and Executive Functions) Act, 1969.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to all Union territories except the Union territory of Chandigarh.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in a Union territory to which it extends on such date^1`
  line `as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in respect thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different areas in a Union territory and any`
  line `reference to the commencement of this Act in relation to a Union territory or an area therein shall mean`
  line `the date on which it comes into force in that Union territory or area.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 2nd October, 1969, vide notification No. S.O. 3836, dated 17th September, 1969 in respect of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `1st March, 1970, vide notification No S.O. 384, Dated 29 January, 1970 in respect of Union territory of Laccadive, Minicoy`
  line `and Amindive Islands.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (27009)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27009&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In sections 3 to 9, "Union territory" means any Union territory other than the Union`
  line `territory of Chandigarh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (27010)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Amendments to Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27010&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of separation of judicial`
  line `and executive functions, the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898), shall in its application to a`
  line `Union territory, be amended in the manner and to the extent specified in the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (27011)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Amendments not to render invalid notifications, etc., before commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27011&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of this Act which amend the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898), so as to alter the`
  line `manner in which, the authority by which, or the law under or in accordance with which, any powers are`
  line `exercisable, shall not render invalid any notification, order, commitment, attachment, bye-law, rule or`
  line `regulation duly made or issued or anything duly done before the commencement of this Act, and any such`
  line `notification, order, commitment, attachment, bye-law, rule or regulation or thing may be revoked, varied`
  line `or undone in the like manner, to the like extent and in the like circumstances, as if it had been duly made,`
  line `issued or done after the commencement of this Act by the competent authority and in accordance with the`
  line `provisions then applicable to such case.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (27012)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions exercisable by Judicial and Executive Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27012&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where under any law the`
  line `functions exercisable by a Magistrate relate to matters which involve the appreciation or sifting of`
  line `evidence or the formulation of any decision which exposes any person to any punishment, or penalty, or`
  line `detention in custody pending investigation, inquiry or trial or would have the effect of sending him for`
  line `trial before any Court, such functions shall, subject to the provisions of this Act and the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898) as amended by this Act, be exercisable by a Judicial Magistrate and where such functions relate to matters which are administrative or executive in nature, such as the grant of a`
  line `licence, the suspension or cancellation of a licence, sanctioning a prosecution, or withdrawing from a`
  line `prosecution, they shall, subject as aforesaid, be exercisable by an Executive Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (27013)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Repeal of laws in transferred areas in Himachal Pradesh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27013&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `On the commencement of this`
  line `Act in the transferred areas in the Union territory of Himachal Pradesh, the Punjab Separation of`
  line `Judicial and Executive Functions Act, 1964 (Punjab Act 25 of 1964) and the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898^1 (5 of 1898), as in force immediately before such commencement in the said areas shall`
  line `stand repealed except as respects things done or omitted to be done before such repeal under the said`
  line `Punjab Act or under the provisions of the laws amended by the said Punjab Act and section 6 of the`
  line `General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply upon such repeal as if such repeal were a repeal of an`
  line `enactment by a Central Act; and on such commencement, the said Code as amended by this Act shall`
  line `extend to, and come into force in, the said areas and the provisions of the laws (other than the said Code)`
  line `amended by the said Punjab Act shall have effect in the said areas as if such provisions had not been`
  line `amended by the said Punjab Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "transferred areas" means the territories added to the Union territory`
  line `of Himachal Pradesh by sub-section (1) of section 5 of the Punjab Reorganisation Act, 1966 (31 of 1966),`
  line `except the territories comprised in the districts of Lahaul and Spiti.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (27014)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27014&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as provided in this section, nothing in this Act shall be deemed to affect—`
  line
  line `(a) the validity, invalidity, effect or consequence of anything done or suffered to be done before`
  line `the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred before such`
  line commencement;
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred or inflicted in respect of any act before such`
  line commencement;
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of such right, privilege, obligation,`
  line `liability, penality, forfeiture or punishment,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced and any`
  line `such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed in accordance with the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure,1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898), as amended by this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All legal proceedings pending before a Magistrate or Court immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall, if such Magistrate or Court ceases to have jurisdiction in respect of such`
  line `proceedings under the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898) as amended by this`
  line `Act, stand on such commencement transferred to the Magistrate or Court having jurisdiction under the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898), as amended by this Act and shall be`
  line `heard and disposed of by such Magistrate or Court and such Magistrate or Court shall have all the powers`
  line `and jurisdiction in respect thereof as if they had been originally instituted before such Magistrate or in`
  line `such Court, including the power of the succeeding Magistrate under section 350 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898^1`
  line `(5 of 1898).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (27015)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27015&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government, in consultation with the High Court having jurisdiction in relation to the`
  line `Union territory concerned, may, by order, do anything (including the specification of the appropriate Magistrate, whether judicial or executive, having jurisdiction under any law) not inconsistent with such`
  line `provisions for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of three years from the commencement`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— In this section, "High Court" shall have the same meaning as in clause (i) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (27016)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Legislative Assembly of Union territory to amend this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103&sectionId=27016&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00042_196919_1517807324103
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in section 21 of the Government of Union Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963), the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of a Union territory may by law amend this Act in its application to that Union`
  line territory.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
